# CI Workflow Triggers

> **Full docs:** [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) — update that file when changing CI (see [`ci-documentation.mdc`](ci-documentation.mdc)).

## Build & Test — PR (`.github/workflows/build.yml`)

| Job | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Detect changes | path filters (`native`, `typescript`, `workflows`) |
| Typecheck & lint | `run-pr-quality.sh` on `self-hosted` + Node 20 (no ci-build pull) |
| Compile native | debug `.node` — **only** when `native` or `workflows` paths change |
| Build TypeScript | `npm run build:ts` — **only** when `typescript` or `workflows` paths change |
| Test | restores native + TS dist caches; runs cargo + npm tests (fallback compile/build on cache miss) |

`compile-native` and `build-ts` run **in parallel** after quality passes. TS-only PRs skip native compile; Rust-only PRs skip TS build. Vitest imports `src/` directly, but `build:ts` still validates publishable output when TS changes.

Runs on **pull_request → `main`** only. Linux x64 jobs use **`self-hosted`**; macOS/Windows stay on GitHub-hosted runners.

## Build & Test — main (`.github/workflows/build-main.yml`)

Runs on **push → `main`**: reusable release matrix (`reusable-build-linux`, `reusable-build-host`) → `reusable-test`.

## Release (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)

Runs on **`release/*` tag push**: same reusable build/test workflows → npm publish → GitHub Release.

## Reusable workflows & composite actions

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `reusable-build-linux.yml` | Linux release matrix (3 targets) |
| `reusable-build-host.yml` | macOS + Windows release matrix |
| `reusable-test.yml` | DinD test job (`coturn/coturn` + `ci-build`) |
| `actions/ci-build-native-linux` | Cache, compile, verify, upload (Linux) |
| `actions/ci-build-native-host` | Toolchain setup + compile (host OS) |
| `actions/ci-cache-ts-dist` | sdk/signaling `dist/` cache restore/save |
| `actions/ci-run-integration-tests` | coturn sidecar + ci-build test run |
| `actions/native-binding-cache` | Per-target `.node` cache restore/save |

## CI Docker image (`ci` branch)

Rebuild `ghcr.io/.../ci-build:latest` when `docker/ci/Dockerfile` changes — push to **`ci`** branch or **`workflow_dispatch`** on CI Docker image workflow.

## Local validation

```bash
npm run ci:verify:linux          # release cross-builds (matches main push)
npm run ci:verify:checks:docker  # PR quality + integration checks
npm run ci:verify                # both
```

After changing `docker/ci/Dockerfile`, rebuild (`npm run ci:docker:build`) and push to `ci` branch.
